Ed Miliband confirmed he would press on with controversial plans to cap rents . 
  He said rent controls would give millions of ‘forgotten’ renters a fairer deal . 
  But Generation Rent campaign group said his plans were ‘riddled with loopholes’ Landlords would have to offer three-year tenancies and would be banned from raising rent above inflation . 
  Tories called the proposal ‘drivel’ and said it would suppress house building and push rents up . 
 